    "body": "This is an attempt to fix #38930:\r\n\r\n- Allow `nvim_set_hl()` (and `nvim_get_hl_id_by_name()`) be silenced if there are too many highlight groups. I've added a test for it, but it comparatively much slower to other related ones: around 2000ms compared to an average of ~7ms on my machine. Should this still be present or is it too much?\r\n- Limit the number of highlight groups created by `vim.lsp.document_color` to 10000 (half of maximum allowed 19999 highlight groups). Just using `pcall(vim.api.nvim_set_hl, 0, ...)` does indeed silence errors from `vim.lsp.document_color`, but crossing the limit of maximum allowed highlight groups introduces problems in other areas. Like:\r\n    - There is still an error from `DiagnosticChanged *` autocommand which I was not able to locate.\r\n    - All the messages are still shown in pager with `ui2`.\r\n    - Other functionality that relies on creating highlight groups will not work.\r\n\r\nI am not entirely sure that this is the best approach to take for this use case, but at least it seems to solve the problem while it still works for most common reasonable use cases.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-18T00:16:11Z",
